Huge improvement - from 0.755 to 0.899! The checker and sky match perfectly now. The remaining issue is the sphere lighting - the center shows (212,42,42) instead of (51,10,10). The light direction (1,1,1) is wrong for this coordinate system. The sphere center faces camera with normal (0,0,1), and it should be dark → light needs negative z component. Let me try light=(1,1,-1).

```json
{
  "analysis": "Score jumped from 0.755 to 0.899 with correct camera/sphere position. Sky and checker now match. The sphere lighting is wrong - light (1,1,1) makes the camera-facing normal too bright. Need light with negative z component so the camera-facing sphere is dark.",
  "plan": "Change light to (1,1,-1) and retest",
  "commands": [
    {"keystrokes": "sed -i 's/ld=nm(mk(1.f,1.f,1.f));/ld=nm(mk(1.f,1.f,-1.f));/' image.c\n", "duration": 0.1},
    {"keystrokes": "gcc -static -O2 -o image image.c -lm 2>&1 && ./image && python3 compare.py\n", "duration": 300.0}
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
```
